This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross-lingual sequence tagging. Additionally, the paper uses adversarial training, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the purview of cs.CL. 

The paper also uses neural networks for training, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper experiments with different types of adversarial training, which involves optimizing a loss function, making it likely to belong to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper deals with tasks such as dependency parsing and sentence compression, which involve analyzing and processing visual data, making it possible for the paper to belong to the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
